So back on topic. Yes, current political culture politicians certainly will run away screaming from anything resembling a hot potato, so there's probably not much to wait for from that quarter. At least not for the time being.<br>
But I don't think big business will have a go at it either. Same reasons: long term and a gamble. And apart from the political sphere the obstacles for big business are structural. There are no safe returns in a reasonable short amount of time and the perspective of a CEO tends to be a quarter at a time. So there will always be more lucrative and safer options for finance to put its investments, especially on an increasingly globalized market. Truth is space (and thus nuclear propulsion) is just too big for free market capitalism. It needs government and state power to pave the way.<br>
Maybe stable, long term government run by the wiser rather than the many is part of the answer?<br>
